CN: 搭档，这是你上次出任务错过的课程笔记和作业。
EN: Partner, here are my notes and the homework you missed while you were away.

CN: 记得补交。
EN: Don't forget to do your assignment.

CN: 有些事情过去了就让它过去吧……
EN: Let's just forget about it...

CN: 有些事情过去了就让它过去吧……
EN: Let's just forget about it...

CN: 我这怎么突然信号不好了
EN: Sorry, my connection's not stable.

CN: 我这怎么突然信号不好了
EN: Sorry, my connection's not stable. Your last message didn't go through.

CN: 哦是吗？忘了告诉你，朵尔老师就在我旁边看着。
EN: Oh really? By the way, I forgot to tell you something. Teacher Doll is right beside me, watching.

CN: 突然涌出了一股熊熊燃烧的学习热情。
EN: Uh... WOW! I suddenly feel REALLY EXCITED to learn today!

CN: 突然涌出了一股熊熊燃烧的学习热情。
EN: Uh... WOW! I suddenly feel REALLY EXCITED to learn today!

CN: 居然有被我落下的作业，这怎么能坐视不管呢？
EN: I can't believe I forgot about my homework! I better get to work and finish it all before I'm late!

CN: 既然如此，好搭档你一定会帮我补课的对吧？
EN: So, Partner! You'll help me catch up, right?!

CN: 对吧？!
EN: R-right?!

CN: 没问题，这是作为搭档应该做的。
EN: Of course. That's what partners are supposed to do.

CN: 朵尔老师也很欣慰，决定给你设计一套独家附加题呢。
EN: Teacher Doll is also pleased, and told me to tell you that she'll be adding some additional bonus questions just for you.

CN: 居然有这样的机会时时与你联系。
EN: I'm so glad we'll have more opportunities to work together in the future.

CN: 这实在是……
EN: That's...

CN: 替我谢谢那个朵尔。
EN: Tell Doll I said thanks...

CN: 虽然没有什么帮忙的需要。
EN: Even if there aren't any pressing matters...

CN: 但我想念你时，可以给你发消息吗？
EN: Is it alright if I send you a message?

CN: 我们永远是好搭档。
EN: We will always be good partners.

CN: ……如果我给你发消息太频繁，会打扰到你吗？
EN: ...Would it bother you if I send you too many messages?

CN: %player%，你的成绩出来了。
EN: %player%, your test results are in.

CN: 知道你多少分吗？
EN: Would you like to guess how you did?

CN: ……你这样我压力很大。
EN: ...Y-you're stressing me out here...

CN: ……你这样我压力很大。
EN: ...Y-you're stressing me out here...

CN: 我是来恭喜你的。虽然这学期发生了很多事，但你目前为止的表现还算不错。
EN: Don't worry, I'm here to congratulate you. Despite all of the "incidents" you've had this term, you did SUCH a good job on this test.

CN: 作为奖励，我调整了一下你的训练计划，接下来几天就好好休息吧。
EN: In fact, you did such a good job that you deserve a reward. I've personally adjusted your upcoming training schedule. Enjoy your time off~.

CN: 对不起我错了我假期一定努力补休。
EN: I'm sorry, I messed up. I'll work hard during my break...

CN: 对不起我错了我假期一定努力补休。
EN: I'm sorry, I messed up. I'll work hard during my break...

CN: 我本来是来恭喜你的。虽然这学期发生了很多事，但你目前为止的表现还算不错。
EN: Don't worry, I'm here to congratulate you. Despite all of the "incidents" you've had this term, you did SUCH a good job on this test.

CN: 不过既然你主动提出补休，那我也不介意加点班。
EN: Since you've asked to take some time off, I don't mind giving you some extra lessons after class to make up for your time off.

CN: 别客气，就这么说定了。明天课上再见。
EN: Don't worry, it's no trouble at all. See you tomorrow~.

CN: 我假期还有其他训练的啊——
EN: I have other training sessions already scheduled on my time off—

CN: 我假期还有其他训练的啊——
EN: I have other training sessions already scheduled on my time off—

CN: 开玩笑的。
EN: I'm joking.

CN: 我调整了一下你的训练计划，接下来几天就好好休息吧。
EN: I've adjusted your training schedule. Go enjoy your break over the next few days.

CN: 开动你聪明的小脑袋猜一猜。
EN: You're smart. Why not guess and see if you can figure it out?

CN: 知道通讯器，你是校内人？
EN: Well, you know about the communicator. Are you a student?

CN: 怎么不算呢，如果大家还愿意承认的话。
EN: Sure, why not? That's what everyone says anyways.

CN: 你是那个朵尔。
EN: You're that Doll!

CN: 你是……那个朵尔。
EN: Wait... you're that Doll aren't you?!

CN: 答对了，聪明的狗狗有奖励。
EN: You got it~! A smart dog like you deserves a reward.

CN: 什么奖励？
EN: A reward?

CN: ……什么奖励？
EN: ...A reward?

CN: 奖励一个摸头，欢迎随时来黑池领取。
EN: Your reward is a pat on the head. Come to the Black Pool whenever you want to redeem your prize.

CN: 我会和校方反映的。
EN: I'm reporting this to the school authorities.

CN: ……我会和校方反映这个漏洞的。
EN: ...I'm reporting this loophole you found to the school authorities.

CN: 真是坏孩子，不过你以为这种小东西能够拦住我吗？
EN: My, what a naughty child. You don't really think this little thing can hold me forever, do you?

CN: 我会一直看着你的。
EN: I will ALWAYS be watching you.

CN: 怎么了，奥吉尔？
EN: What's the matter, Ogier?

CN: 哇，真的有字耶。
EN: Wow, it's actually working...

CN: 抱歉，主君，刚才我失态了。
EN: Sorry, My Lord. I lost my composure earlier.

CN: 不知道它还能传输什么呢。
EN: I wonder what else it can send.

CN: 还可以发图片！
EN: You can also send images!

CN: 等等，我现在就过去教你。
EN: Hold on. I'll come over and show you.

CN: 我在宿舍。
EN: I'm resting in my dorm room.

CN: 我在宿舍休息，怎么了吗？
EN: I'm resting in my dorm room. What's up?

CN: 休息？
EN: Resting? Really?

CN: 昨天是谁跟我说今天中午要一起特训的？
EN: Now WHO was the one that told me we'd be having special training together at noon today?

CN: 现在你说休息？
EN: And now you're telling me you're RESTING?

CN: 糟了……
EN: Uh...

CN: 糟了……
EN: Uh...

CN: 你肯定记错了
EN: You must have misremembered.

CN: 你肯定记错了，肯定是艾尔瓦说的。
EN: You must have misremembered. I'm pretty sure Alva was the one who was going to train with you.

CN: 好啊你这家伙，给我等着。
EN: Alright, that's it. Wait right there.

CN: 她上午说了句什么巧克力咔哒咔哒的，就跑了出去，一直到现在都没有回来。
EN: She mentioned something about "chocolate crunch" this morning and left. Now I can't find her.

CN: 礼物？
EN: A gift?

CN: 可是现在也不是什么节日，难道是我忘了……
EN: But it's not even a holiday... right?

CN: 我觉得……
EN: Well...

CN: 我觉得，有时候，礼物不一定是非要节日才能购买的。
EN: Well, you can someone buy a gift even if it's not a holiday.

CN: 这样么……那我也准备点什么吧。
EN: Is that right... OK, then I'll get a gift for Jenkin too.

CN: 抱歉抱歉，我还不太会用键盘。
EN: Sorry about that. I'm still getting used to using a keyboard.

CN: 多练习就好了。
EN: Practice makes pefect. You'll figure it out in no time.

CN: 没事，我一开始用的时候也磕磕绊绊的，多练习几次就好。
EN: It's fine. I also made mistakes when I started out. Just keep practicing and you'll eventually figure it out.

CN: 唉，虽然是这样，但我怕我明天就忘记了。
EN: Yes, but... I'm afraid I'll forget everything I learned by tomorrow.

CN: 那就多来几次！
EN: Then do it even more!

CN: 那就多来几次，总没问题的！
EN: Then just do it even more! It'll be fine!

CN: 我不是艾尔瓦。
EN: I'm not Alva.

CN: ……那个，我不是艾尔瓦。
EN: Uh... I'm not Alva.

CN: 我是守密人。
EN: Actually, I'm the Keeper.

CN: 我是守密人。
EN: Actually, I'm the Keeper.

CN: 这次我一定不会忘记了，一定！
EN: I definitely won't forget next time! Definitely!

CN: 守密人，非常感谢您昨日送来疗养院的物资，也请替我谢谢德克斯特勋爵一直以来的资助。
EN: Keeper, thank you for bringing those supplies to the sanatorium yesterday. Please thank Lord Dexter for his continued support.

CN: 这是我们应该做的。
EN: No problem. It's what we should do.

CN: 这是我们应该做的。
EN: No problem. It's what we should do.

CN: 一个人管理疗养院，你辛苦了。
EN: It must be difficult having to manage the sanatorium all by yourself.

CN: 一个人管理疗养院，你辛苦了。
EN: It must be difficult having to manage the sanatorium all by yourself.

CN: 我做的事情不算什么。
EN: It's nothing, really.

CN: 我会打扫好院长的办公室等着你们。
EN: I'll clean the dean's office and wait for you.

CN: 这也是我唯一能为那孩子做的了。
EN: That's all I can do for her...

CN: 艾继丝和詹金、带来了两个圆圆的东西。
EN: Aigis and Jenkin brought over two round things.

CN: 它们像脓疱一样，但轻轻的，里面空空的，会飘起来……
EN: They look like pustules, but they're light, hollow inside, and can float.

CN: 对，就是气球！
EN: Yes, it's a balloon!

CN: 主人要来和莉莉一起玩气球吗？
EN: Master, would you like to come over and play with the balloons together with Lily?

CN: 好的，你在哪里？
EN: Sure. Where are you?

CN: 好的，你在哪里？
EN: Sure. Where are you?

CN: 刚才、刚才……脓疱钻到气球里了……
EN: Just now... one of the pustules crawled into the balloon... It's floating away...

CN: 在茜尔维亚这里，主人快一起来，救救脓疱……
EN: I'm at Sylvia's... Master, come over quickly and save them...

CN: 叮叮~女仆珈伦的贴心小提示：你的早饭已经放在门口了哦！
EN: Ding-ding~! Your wonderful Maid Karen here letting you know that your breakfast is at your door whenever you get up~!

CN: 是不是你拿走了我的衣服？
EN: Did you take my clothes!?

CN: 你！是不是你拿走了我的衣服？
EN: Hey! Did you take my clothes!?

CN: 哎呀主人，你怎么这么早就醒了？衣服还没干呢！
EN: Oh dear, Master. Why are you already awake? Your clothes haven't dried yet!

CN: 你拿去洗了？
EN: "Haven't dried yet"? Are you washing my clothes?

CN: 还没干？你是拿去洗了？
EN: "Haven't dried yet"? Are you washing my clothes?

CN: 当然啦！一个合格的女仆怎么能坐视自己的主人穿着脏兮兮皱巴巴的衣服出门呢？
EN: Of course! As a qualified maid, I couldn't possibly let my Master go out wearing dirty, wrinkled clothing!

CN: 所以人家特别一夜没睡，帮你把每一件衣服都洗得干、干、净、净、哦。
EN: So I stayed up all~ night and washed all of your clothes tho~rough~ly~!

CN: 倒是给我留一件！
EN: Leave some clothes for me to wear at least!

CN: 那也不能全洗了啊，你倒是给我留一件！
EN: You can't just wash everything and leave nothing for me to wear!

CN: 主人身上不是还有一件嘛，说实话我是很想偷偷脱下来的，但主人睡觉的时候被子裹得好紧，害得人家都无从下手呢。
EN: Well, Master DOES still have some clothes. Honestly, I really wanted to wash that too, but... Master was wrapped up so snugly in bed that I couldn't take it off without waking you up~.

CN: 让我来！珈伦可是万能的女仆，从洗衣服到换锁到所有的一切都能完成！
EN: Oh, leave it to me! Karen is an all-purpose maid, capable of handling everything from laundry to lock changes or anything else~!

CN: 不！你别过来！
EN: No! Do NOT come in my room!

CN: 不！你别过来！
EN: No! Do NOT come in my room!

CN: 不要不好意思嘛！我马上就到哦~
EN: Don't be so shy! I'll be there in a moment~!

CN: 我……有点困惑。
EN: I'm... a bit confused.

CN: 开始压榨人了……！
EN: Exploiting you already, huh?

CN: 开始压榨人了……！
EN: Exploiting you already, huh?

CN: 哈哈哈，倒不是。是我提出想要帮忙，但，我也不知道自己能做什么。
EN: Hahaha... it's not like that. I'm the one that offered to help, but... I'm not sure what I can do to help...

CN: 我做了一辈子士兵，只会听从命令。就算是在勒姆瓦希，大多数时候我也不确定自己该做什么，能做什么。
EN: I've been a soldier my entire life; just following other people's orders. Even when I was in Remouahe, I was never really sure about what I should do.

CN: 现在突然告诉我，我可以自己决定一切，这感觉……让我很陌生。
EN: Suddenly being told to decide what to do myself... It's a new experience for me.

CN: 朵尔小姐大概是担心我不适应，才会这么问的吧。
EN: Miss Doll probably asked because she was worried that I wouldn't be able to adapt to civilian life.

CN: 她虽然看上去冷漠，其实还是很体恤他人的。
EN: She may appear cold, but she's actually quite considerate of others.

CN: 真是少见的评价。
EN: Haven't heard that before.

CN: ……真是少见的评价。
EN: ...Haven't heard that before.

CN: 如果实在没有头绪的话，就从擅长的地方做起如何？
EN: Well, if you're still unsure, how about starting with what you're good at?

CN: 艾尔瓦在训练士兵上很有一手吧。
EN: Considering your background, I'd say you're quite skilled at training soldiers. Why not start there?

CN: 训练么，说的也是。或许……我知道了。
EN: Training, you say. That... could work.

CN: 今晚十点，地下教室，绝密聚会，全新玩法，刺激体验，就等你来。
EN: Tonight at 10 o'clock, in the underground classroom: a secret party, a new game; an exciting experience awaits you!

CN: 哎呀，好像点错了群发的对象。
EN: Oops, it seems I sent this message to the wrong person.

CN: 你绝对又在做什么违法的事吧！
EN: You're doing something illegal again aren't you?!

CN: 你绝对又在做什么违法的事吧！
EN: You're doing something illegal again aren't you?!

CN: 怎么会呢，只是大家课余时间一点放松的小娱乐而已。
EN: Whaaaat? No, no, not at all! It's just a bit of light entertainment for everyone to relax during their off time.

CN: 当然也非常欢迎守密人一起来玩，我会很期待的。
EN: You're welcome to join us as well, Keeper. I'd love to go a few rounds with you.

CN: 我看起来像傻子吗？
EN: Do I look like a idiot?

CN: 我看起来很像傻子吗，我是不会和你“玩”这个的。
EN: Do I look like an idiot? I won't "play" with you.

CN: 我哪有那么可怕，对自己自信一点嘛。
EN: Hey now, I'm not THAT scary. You should have more confidence in yourself!

CN: 总之我就当没看见。
EN: Whatever. I'll just pretend I didn't see that message.

CN: 总之我就当没看见。
EN: Whatever. I'll just pretend I didn't see that message.

CN: 没有反手举报我已经很讲情分了。
EN: Be grateful I didn't decide to report you.

CN: 没有反手举报我已经很讲情分了。
EN: Be grateful I didn't decide to report you.

CN: 你低调点，小心下次发到朵尔那里，你就等着去喝咖啡吧。
EN: Be more careful next time, or your message might find its way to Miss Doll and you'll get to have a secret party in an underground cell.

CN: 谢谢体贴的华生~
EN: Thanks for the advice, my thoughtful Watson~.

CN: 什么时候改变主意了可以随时来玩哦。
EN: If you ever change your mind, you know where I'll be~.

CN: 呀，让我看看这是什么好东西。
EN: Mmm... let me see if this thing works...

CN: 有欲求不满的家伙想念我的小皮鞭了？
EN: Is there someone out there who's unfulfilled and needs a little bit of my whip?

CN: 别害羞嘛，不要掩藏自己内心深处的欲望。
EN: Don't be shy! Don't hide your desires!

CN: 顺从它，释放它，点燃它！
EN: Yield to them! Free them! Let them run wild!

CN: 在疼痛里尽情叫喊吧！
EN: LET LOOSE YOUR DESIRES!

CN: 我要关机了。
EN: ...I'm turning my phone off.

CN: 我要关机了。
EN: ...I'm turning my phone off.

CN: 难得有这么方便又私密的联系方式，别害怕，没人会知道的。
EN: It's quite rare to find such a convenient and private way to talk with you. Don't be afraid; it's our little secret.

CN: 随时可以找我提供上门服务哦！
EN: If you ever need some private service, you can call me over anytime!

CN: 看来你收到最新的通讯器了，你觉得怎么样？
EN: Looks like you've received the latest communicator. How is it?

CN: 很有意思，也很方便。尽管相隔百里，我们仍能像面对面一般交流。
EN: It's very interesting and convenient. Even though we are hundreds of miles away, we can still communicate as if we were face-to-face.

CN: 如果全世界都能拥有这样的装置，人与人之间的距离一定也不会像现在这样遥远吧。
EN: If the whole world had such devices, the distance between people would not be as vast as it is now.

CN: 不过我明白的，这个技术的特殊性——你知道它是通过与其他精神建立链接来传递信息的吗？
EN: But I understand the uniqueness of this technology—you know it transmits information by connecting our spirits, right?

CN: 我只知道里面有银芯。
EN: I only know there's a Silver Core inside.

CN: 我只知道里面有银芯。
EN: I only know there's a Silver Core inside.

CN: 你是看到了吗？
EN: Did you find out how it works?

CN: 你是看到了吗？
EN: Did you find out how it works?

CN: 正是如此，我们的精神与银芯相连，银芯则与其他同类装置中的银芯相连。
EN: Indeed. Our spirits connect to a Silver Core, which is then linked to the Cores in other similar devices.

CN: 不得不说，非常精妙。
EN: I must say, it is quite ingenious.

CN: 有内幕消息。
EN: I have insider information...

CN: 事关肖尔迪奇猎场所有权归属以及租赁转让事宜。
EN: ...in regards to the ownership and lease transfer of the Shoreditch Hunting Grounds.

CN: 抱歉，不小心发错人了。希望这些大人的无聊琐事没有打扰到你的心情。
EN: Sorry. I accidentally sent it to the wrong person. I hope this boring adult matter didn't bother you.

CN: 别太见外，我想听内幕。
EN: Don't stop now. I want to hear more!

CN: 别太见外，我想听内幕。
EN: Don't stop now. I want to hear more!

CN: 如果你真的有兴趣的话……我倒是留了一小片蔷薇园，可以免费赠予你。
EN: If you're interested... I happen to have a small rose garden that I can give you. No charge.

CN: 很遗憾，索蕾尔夫人。守密人不能接受任何价值超过■■的礼物，不管作何用途。
EN: Unfortunately, Ms. Sorel... As a Keeper, I cannot accept any gifts valued over ■■, no matter what the reason may be.

CN: 真是死板的规定。本想找一个值得信赖的人代为打理蔷薇……
EN: What a rigid rule. I wanted someone I could trust to tend the roses...

CN: 小菜一碟！交给我吧~
EN: No problem! Leave it to me~.

CN: 打理蔷薇？小菜一碟！交给我吧~
EN: Tending roses? No problem! Leave it to me~.

CN: 前提是没有课程和任务的时候。
EN: As long as you aren't busy with your classes or missions.

CN: 你有一颗蔷薇般柔软的心，守密人%player%%sirormadam%。
EN: Your heart is as beautiful as a rose, {Male=Mr.,Female=Miss} %player%.

CN: 有什么事吗，小艾继丝？
EN: What's up, little Aigis?

CN: 艾继丝做了糖果，想在下午的茶会分给大家…
EN: Aigis made candies she wanted to share at the afternoon tea party...

CN: 守密人没空的话，我悄悄给你留一点…
EN: If the Keeper is busy, I can secretly set some aside for you...

CN: 我会认真品尝的。
EN: I'd love that.

CN: 谢谢你，小艾继丝，我会认真品尝的。
EN: Thank you, little Aigis. I'd love that.

CN: 喂，你这家伙，怎么敢这么对待艾继丝精心准备的礼物！
EN: Hey, you! How dare you brush aside Aigis's invitation like that!

CN: 听着，下午的差会上钥匙看不到你，我就让布朗把糖果全部偷走！
EN: Listen up! If I don't see you at the tea party this afternoon, I'll have Brown steal all your candy!

CN: 哼哼，这就甘拜下风了？
EN: Giving up so soon?

CN: 为什么……
EN: How..?

CN: 为什么，为什么来自原始部族的女王……
EN: How could a queen from an ancient tribe...

CN: 牌技比现代人还要精湛啊……
EN: ...have card skills better than even a modern day person?!

CN: 我能告诉你的只有，这都是熟能生巧，亲爱的小家伙。
EN: All I can say is that practice makes perfect, my dear little one.

CN: 等你到我这个年纪的时候，自然就知道了~
EN: When you reach my age, you'll understand~.

EN: Everyone's worried about you...

CN: 可以呀，一会儿在校门口见。

CN: 那还用说？排了我好久。

CN: 我就是一大早搬凳子去排队的闲人。
EN: I too am someone with nothing better to do then stand in a line early in the morning...

EN: When you bought a whole dozen cupcakes, I bet you weren't expecting me to be watching from the back, did you?

CN: 是个惊喜哦。
EN: Surprise.

EN: Smartass... Fine, I won't tell anyone about what you did this morning.

CN: 你怎么也有一个通讯器？

EN: Mythag aren't the only ones who have mastered Silver Core tech.

EN: Chief Priest, please be mindful of your status. Please don't imitate charlatans...

EN: Juliette suggested that in order to increase number of followers, we need to adopt a gentler and more proactive approach to our preaching.

CN: 我想，她的话不无道理。
EN: I think there is merit in that suggestion.

EN: As long as it can spread the grace of our Lord, I'm willing to imitate any modern methods.

EN: It doesn't matter. If it's to spread my Lord's grace, I won't give up even on the most stubborn of people.

EN: As someone who is deeply linked with my Lord, I hope Keeper %sirormadam% attends on time.

CN: 怎么了吗？

EN: What's wrong?

CN: 不介意的话，可以跟我说说？
EN: Would you like to talk about it?

EN: She even wants to follow me into the restroom. It's a bit embarrassing.

EN: I should have guessed. You're the only person who would give me something like this.

EN: Like all art, sculpting is also a very personal thing.

EN: Not everyone can see these stone creations as an extension of themselves; a continuation of their life like I do.

EN: Apparently, this remedy can grant me power similar to Lord Goliath's.

CN: 那是好事啊，就是怎么感觉有点可疑？
EN: Sounds good, but... it seems too good to be true...

EN: You may envy me, but I'll accept those feelings. I'll go ahead and take it.

EN: Uh... Not sure why you'd think that, but good luck I guess.

EN: I need fifty to buy the remedy. Consider it an investment.

EN: Once my power awakens, I'll repay you a hundredfold.

EN: Are you feeling bored? Tired?! Like the world is just passing you by?!

CN: 卡茜亚，你又在搞什么？
EN: ...what are you on about, Casiah?

EN: Well fret no more! The great master of magic Casiah is here to offer you a once in a lifetime opportunity that you won't want to miss!

EN: It's my great pleasure to announce to you that the great Casiah's Magical Carnival is about to begin!

EN: Did you mean to send this to me?

EN: Whether it be turning nothing into something, something into nothing, changing stone to gold, or even transforming the human form—whatever your wildest imagination could possibly dream of, the magic of the great Master Casiah is guaranteed to excite and amaze!

EN: Order a ticket now to enjoy a 20% discount! Limited slots available; first come, first served. We look forward to welcoming you to... the GREAT MAGICAL CARNIVAL!

CN: 我已经为你预备了特等席。
EN: I've got a special seat reserved just for you.

EN: I expect you to keep your promise.

EN: It's fine. She'll be fine after a reboot.

CN: 好吧。
EN: OK.

CN: 毕竟弥萨格的成员也越来越多了。
EN: Well, Mythag's population has been increasing after all.

EN: That explains it. I was wondering why there were always people there when I was going to practice.

EN: I have a little performance at the Mythag Hall in a month and I'd like to have someone listen to it before I perform.

CN: 所以……
EN: So... if it's not too much trouble...

CN: 好吧。
EN: Sure.

CN: 好吧，一会儿在礼堂见？
EN: Sure. Meet you at the auditorium?

CN: 你同意了吗？太好了。一会儿见。
EN: Really? Great! See you soon!

CN: 我最近收获了一条珍贵的、马鬃毛制成的皮鞭，有兴趣来体验一下吗？
EN: I recently added a special horsehair whip to my collection. Would you be interested in trying it out?

CN: 忙。
EN: Busy right now.

CN: 忙
EN: Busy right now.

CN: 不好意思，忙。
EN: Sorry, I'm doing something right now...

CN: 不好意思，忙
EN: Sorry, I'm doing something right now...

CN: 真叫人伤心。看来只能去校园里转转，看看有没有其他感兴趣的同好……
EN: How unfortunate. Oh well, I suppose I'll wander around the campus and see if I can find someone else who is interested...

CN: 等一下，旺达夫人！请你待在原地不要走动。
EN: Wait, Ms. Wanda! Don't go anywhere.

CN: 我现在过来。
EN: I'm coming over.

CN: 真是个口是心非的孩子。
EN: How cute. Were you playing hard to get~?

CN: ■■礼拜堂门口，不见不散~
EN: I'll be at the chapel. Don't make me wait long~.

CN: 守咪人，守咪人在吗？在吗守咪人？
EN: Keeper. Keeper! You there? Are you, are you?!

CN: ……是守密人。
EN: ...Yes, I'm here.

CN: ……是守密人。
EN: ...Yes, I'm here.

CN: 哎呀不是差不多嘛。
EN: Oh, so you are.

CN: 守咪人不在。
EN: No, I'm not here.

CN: 守咪人不在。
EN: No, I'm not here.

CN: 骗人，你都回信了！
EN: You liar! You literally just replied to me!

CN: 在那辆电车上，您写下了一段诗句……
EN: I remember that you wrote a verse on that tram...

CN: 不堪回首。
EN: Embarassing...

CN: 死去的记忆开始攻击我……
EN: It's embarassing being reminded of that...

CN: 伟大的作品。
EN: I thought it was so good, but...

CN: 如此伟大的作品，那只毛毛虫竟然不允许我入座。没品！
EN: I thought it was so good, but that caterpillar refused to let me sit! That hack!

CN: 回来以后，我仔细思考了。
EN: After we returned, I thought long and hard.

CN: 虽然用传统的眼光看来，那段诗句与美感之间缺乏必要的联系。
EN: Although that verse was certainly "bad" when viewed through the traditional lens...

CN: 但不和谐、讽刺、错误，这些也应该是诗歌的一部分。
EN: ...I believe that things like dissonance, irony, and errors can also be part of poetry!

CN: 在我的新诗集里，我希望能把您这句诗加进去。
EN: I'd love to include your verse in my new poetry collection.

CN: 可以吗，守密人%sirormadam%？
EN: Is that okay, Keeper %sirormadam%?

CN: 你认真的？
EN: Wait, seriously?

CN: 你认真的？
EN: Wait, seriously?

CN: 当然！
EN: Absolutely!

CN: ……这就是天才诗人的觉悟吗？
EN: ...Is this the birth of a new genius poet?

CN: 你可能是最近写东西写得太累了。好好休息吧！
EN: Well, you might be tired from writing too much. Rest up!

CN: 稿费记得给我
EN: Don't forget my royalties!

CN: 没问题！发表以后记得把稿费分我。
EN: No problem! Don't forget my royalties after it's published!

CN: 茜尔维亚小姐明令禁止了。
EN: It's not my fault!

CN: 不是我不给你，只是茜尔维亚女士明令禁止了，你不能再超量喝咖啡了。
EN: It's not my fault! Ms. Sylvia has strictly forbidden you from drinking more coffee.

CN: 你不能再超量喝咖啡了。
EN: It's Ms. Sylvia, not me!

CN: 不是我不给你，只是茜尔维亚女士明令禁止了，你不能再超量喝咖啡了。
EN: It's Ms. Sylvia, not me! She said you're forbidden from having any more caffeine.

CN: 可是我的眼皮已经不受我的控制了！
EN: But I can't control my eyelids any longer!

CN: 要是我一个不小心真的闭上眼睛进入黑暗怎么办，黑色的恐怖会找上我，黑色的死亡会找上我，然后我的生命我的精神我的一切
EN: What if I accidentally close my eyes and fall asleep?! The black terror will find me, the black death will find me! My life, soul, everything; GONE!

CN: 我知道了。
EN: Wait. I know...

CN: 用胶水把眼睛粘起来，就不会一不小心睡着了。
EN: I'll just glue my eyelids open so they CAN'T close.

CN: 不是？！
EN: No! STOP!

CN: 不是，你住手，这样是不行的！
EN: No! STOP! That won't work!

CN: 这里的音乐教室堪称简陋。
EN: The music room here can only be called rudimentary.

CN: 礼堂也实在是不堪入目。
EN: The hall here is also truly unsightly.

CN: 还有你们的那些乐器，负责维护的人是谁，难道不知道定期调音吗？
EN: And those instruments of yours, who is responsible for maintaining them? Don't they know they require periodic tuning?

CN: 难以置信，这就是高等学府的音乐素养吗？简直让人无法接受。
EN: Unbelievable, is this the musical capacity of a prestigious university? It's simply unacceptable.

CN: 从今天开始，这些东西就由我全面接管了。
EN: From today onward, I shall take on the mantle of overseeing these matters.

CN: 在银霜节之前，我一定要训练出一个合格的乐团。
EN: I must train a qualified orchestra before the Silverfrost Festival.

CN: 幸好我不是乐团成员。
EN: Thank goodness I'm not a member of the orchestra.

CN: 幸好我不是乐团成员。
EN: Thank goodness I'm not a member of the orchestra.

CN: 你也别想走，指挥家。
EN: Don’t think you’re off the hook, Conductor.

CN: 我没有报名啊！
EN: But I never signed up!

CN: %player%，不介意的话，可以让我负责你的心理治疗吗？
EN: %player%, if you don't mind, could I take care of your psychological needs?

CN: ……真的是这样吗？
EN: ...Is that right?

CN: 真的是这样吗？为什么我觉得你另有目的……
EN: Is that right? Why do I feel like you have ulterior motives...

CN: 比如说，借着专属心理医师的名义，窥探我的记忆。
EN: For example, using the guise of a personal psychologist to peer into my memories?

CN: 啊呀，被发现了吗？那就没办法了。
EN: Oh dear, was it that obvious? Oh well, nothing I can do about that.

CN: 但我并不会采取什么过激的手段。相信我。
EN: But I won't do anything extreme. Trust me.

CN: 当然。毕竟我只是个心理医师而已。
EN: Of course. After all, I'm only a psychologist.

CN: ……假期不是才刚开始吗？
EN: ...Didn't it just begin?

CN: ……假期不是才刚开始吗？
EN: ...Didn't it just begin?

CN: 之后的每天，我也会持续维护，保证能够随时开工。
EN: I'll continue maintaining these things every day to ensure we can start work at any time.

CN: 只是指挥学院午饭时的交通……
EN: Does it require that much preparation?

CN: ……只是指挥学院午饭时的交通，也需要做这么多的准备吗？
EN: ...Does it require that much preparation to organize lunch time?

CN: 还有哪片花坛被新来的流浪猫当成了家园，哪片区域又被学生们踩出了新路，哪条道路需要施工维护……
EN: Which flowerbed has the new stray cat taken as its home, which area the students trampled to make a new path, which road needs maintenance...

CN: ……受教了。
EN: ...I see.

CN: ……受教了。看来每份工作都有其意义。
EN: ...I see. It seems every job is important.

CN: 是的，既然我做出选择，就要承担起自己的职责。
EN: Yes. Since I made the choice, I must take responsibility.

CN: 从现在起，我还会每天巡夜，确保假期期间，学院不会出现意外。
EN: From now on, I will patrol every night to ensure that no accidents occur at the academy this break.

CN: 呃，这个，那个，算是都……看了。
EN: Uh, well, I kind of... skimmed them.

CN: 大概，看了……目录。
EN: Well I... probably remember the table of contents.

CN: 大概，看了……目录。
EN: Well I... probably remember the table of contents.

CN: 那些书实在太厚太枯燥了嘛！
EN: The books are just too long and boring!

CN: 那些书实在太厚太枯燥了嘛！密密麻麻的字一看就睡过去了……
EN: The books are just too long and boring! I fall asleep before I can even get past the first page!

CN: 每次看书之后我的睡眠质量倒是很好……
EN: On the bright side, I slept like a baby after reading it...

CN: 算了，之后你来我这里，我一本一本给你讲。
EN: Never mind. Come over and I'll teach you each book myself.

CN: 每天下课后你来我宿舍报道。
EN: Report to my dorm after class every day.

CN: 啊？需要这么认真吗……
EN: Huh? Is it really that serious...?

CN: 啊？需要这么认真吗……
EN: Huh? Is it really that serious...?

CN: 这些都是调查员必读的书籍， 你死记硬背也要学一些。
EN: These are essential books for investigators. You must memorize them, no matter how dull they are.

CN: 我预计每天给你补课一小时，如果你想快点学完，我也不介意陪你通宵读书。
EN: I plan to tutor you for an hour every day. Of course, if you want to learn even faster, we can study together all night.

CN: 还，还是慢点吧……
EN: No, no, an hour is fine!

CN: 还，还是慢点吧……我觉得一个小时就挺好！学太多不利于复习巩固！
EN: No, no, an hour is fine! Too much studying isn't healthy either!

CN: 很好，你的学习态度很不错。
EN: I'm glad to see how enthusiastic you are.

CN: 记得带好笔记本，我会随时检查你的复习情况。
EN: Remember to bring your notebook. I'll be checking your progress.

CN: 我恨我这张破嘴……
EN: Why did I say that...

CN: 打扰了，我思考了很久，想问问你……
EN: Excuse me, I've been thinking for a long time and would like to ask you something...

CN: 你觉得我每次响应你召唤的速度如何？
EN: Do you think I respond to your summons fast enough?

CN: 虽然我每次都注意着你的呼唤，第一时间出发。
EN: Although I always heed your call and set out at as fast as I can...

CN: 但我担心跨越时空的过程会有些许偏差，万一出现了时间的延迟……
EN: ...I'm worried that there might be some deviations during the process of crossing time and space, and if there's a delay...

CN: 我一想到你会因此陷入危险，就有些坐立难安。
EN: The thought of you in peril because of this worries me.

CN: 没有的事，你每次来得都很及时。
EN: You're always there for me.

CN: 知道你会随时在我身后，我一直很安心。
EN: Knowing that you're always there for me gives me peace of mind.

CN: 其实你没必要每次那样急着走……
EN: You don't have to rush off every time...

CN: 不……我不属于这里，留下是一种贪恋，对你、对我，乃至对时空来说都不是好事。
EN: No... I don't belong there. I don't want to build any attachment. It'd be harmful to you, me; even time and space.

CN: 那么，至少多留下一瞬告别的时间吧。
EN: At least set some time aside for me to say goodbye to you before you leave.

CN: 那么，至少多留下一瞬告别的时间吧，让我每次来得及和你说一声再见。
EN: At least set some time aside for me to say goodbye to you before you leave.

CN: 我注意到你最近几门课程作业的评分都有些低，甚至还有逾期提交的。
EN: I've noticed that your grades for the recent assignments have been poor, and you're missing some submissions.

CN: 是发生什么事了吗？还是学习上有什么困难？
EN: Did something happen? Are you facing any difficulties in your studies?

CN: 最近出任务的次数太多了，实在有点累了……
EN: I've been so busy doing missions... I'm so tired...

CN: 最近出任务的次数太多了，实在有点累了……
EN: I've been so busy doing missions... I'm so tired...

CN: 下次我会尽量早点交的。
EN: I'll try to finish my assignments earlier next time.

CN: 好……等等，不交作业？！
EN: Alright... wait, I can skip assignments?!

CN: 你还是朵尔吗？
EN: Is this the real Doll?!

CN: 你还是朵尔吗？
EN: Is this the real Doll?!

CN: 通讯器没有被偷吧？
EN: Did someone steal the communicator?

CN: 通讯器没有被偷吧？
EN: Did someone steal the communicator?

CN: 是什么让你对我产生了这种印象？
EN: Now HOW did you form this impression of me?

CN: 作业不过是督促你们掌握调查员知识的方法，并不能决定你们任何人的能力或价值。
EN: Assignments are merely a method to help you become a skilled investigator. They don't determine one's ability or value.

CN: 如果因为几份作业把弥萨格唯一的守密人累垮了，影响了你的状态，那反而舍本逐末。
EN: It'd be quite the waste to overwork the only Keeper in Mythag over a few assignments.

CN: 如果你觉得自己完全不需要写作业，也可以一直这样申请。
EN: If you believe that you absolutely do not need to do the homework, you are free to keep skipping.

CN: 还有这种好事？！
EN: This seems too good to be true!

CN: 还有这种好事？！
EN: This seems too good to be true!

CN: 当然，你已经不是小孩子了，可以为自己的决定负责。
EN: Of course. You're not a child; you can take responsibility for your decisions.

CN: 我相信你会做出最理性的判断。
EN: I trust you will make the most rational decisions.

CN: 至于现在，先好好休息一下吧。
EN: Now go rest up.

CN: 小狗狗，黑池里好冷啊，我每天都感觉到生命力在流逝。
EN: Oh puppy, it's so cold in the Black Pool. I can feel my life slowly draining away.

CN: 要是你再不来看看我的话，说不定哪天我就会化成融蚀浆消失了。
EN: If you don't visit me soon, I might melt away into D-Slime...

CN: 对师长的关心不是应当的吗？怎么能叫上当呢。
EN: How could you treat your mentor this way? I would never lie to my precious student.

CN: 来抓我的时候，那张正义又天真的脸也很可爱呢。
EN: Your righteous yet naive expression was so~ cute.

CN: 说够了我就把通讯器关掉了。
EN: Stop that or I'm turning my communicator off.

CN: 说够了我就把通讯器关掉了。
EN: Stop that or I'm turning my communicator off.

CN: 唉，真是冷漠啊，无论怎样你都不肯见见我吗？
EN: How cold of you. Is there nothing I can say to have you visit me?

CN: 如果我说，我现在已经把困住我的装置松动了一些呢？
EN: Hmm... What if I say I've managed to loosen the device trapping me a little?

CN: 主君！马厩那匹叫白雪的母温血马最近要到了生产的日子了！
EN: My lord! Mare Snowflake's about to give birth!

CN: 我记得之前那匹公马是纯黑色的，真好奇它们的孩子是什么颜色，会不会是黑白花纹的呢？
EN: I remember that the stallion was pure black. I'm curious about the color of their offspring—will it be black and white?

CN: 也有可能是斑马那样的条纹。
EN: Maybe the foal will have zebra stripes.

CN: 也有可能是斑马那样的条纹。
EN: Maybe the foal will have zebra stripes.

CN: 原，原来还有这种可能吗？真是神奇啊……
EN: Is... is that really possible? That's amazing...

CN: 哈哈哈逗你的！你这种别人说什么都信的习惯很危险啊。
EN: Haha, just kidding! It's dangerous to believe everything other people say.

CN: 我，我下次会注意的！但如果是主君的话，我觉得没有怀疑的必要！
EN: I-I'll be more careful next time! But for you, my lord, I could never doubt your words!

CN: 嗯？对了主君，我打算学习一下相关知识，亲自为白雪接生。
EN: Hmm? By the way, my lord, I'm learning how to and plan on delivering the baby myself!

CN: 一想到能从小参与小马的成长，我就很期待！
EN: I'm looking forward to training the pony!

CN: 原来培养马匹要从这么小开始吗？
EN: Does raising a horse start at such a young age?

CN: 原来培养马匹要从这么小开始吗？
EN: Does raising a horse start at such a young age?

CN: 马对于骑士来说是最亲近的伙伴！与马儿之间的信任当然是越多越好。
EN: A horse is a knight's closest companion! The more trust between them, the better.

CN: 如果到时候我有时间，就和你一起去帮忙吧。
EN: If I have time I'll go and help out.

CN: 呃……可能是因为你的气场太强大了。
EN: Uh... maybe you're just too intimidating.

CN: 呃……可能是因为你的气场太强大了。
EN: Uh... maybe you're just too intimidating.

CN: 大家感觉压力太大。
EN: People might feel too pressured by you.

CN: 果然是这样么，我知道了，我的态度是有那么一点强硬。
EN: Is that how it is? I suppose my attitude might've been abrasive.

CN: 你居然有自知之明？
EN: So you DO have self-awareness...

CN: 你居然有自知之明？
EN: So you DO have self-awareness...

CN: 虽然不只是态度问题吧！
EN: It's not just your attitude!

CN: 虽然不只是态度问题吧！
EN: It's not just your attitude!

CN: 没关系，我已经想到解决办法了。
EN: It's fine. I've got a better idea.

CN: 我来写一批决斗书送到大家的宿舍，这样一定够礼貌了。
EN: I'll write some duel challenges and send them to everyone's dormitories; that should be polite enough.

CN: 就这样决定了，写四十张够不够呢……
EN: It's decided. Is forty enough...?

CN: ？！等等，不是决斗书的问题吧，这也太扰民了！
EN: ?! Hold on, it's not about how you challenge people! This is going way too far!

CN: ？！等等，不是决斗书的问题吧，这也太扰民了！
EN: ?! Hold on, it's not about how you challenge people! This is going way too far!

CN: 你不懂，我听德克斯特说过，在过去通过决斗书战斗可是绅士的行为，学着点吧年轻人！
EN: You don't understand. I heard Dexter say that in the past, challenging people to duels by way of a written challenge was considered a gentleman's act. You should learn from your ancestors, young man!

CN: 不是，你，我，总之别去啊啊啊！
EN: No, you... I... stop!

CN: 不是，你，我，总之别去啊啊啊！
EN: No, you... I... stop!

CN: 你知道这样一顶小小的黑色礼帽是属于谁的吗？
EN: Do you know who the owner of this small black top hat might be?

CN: 这个尺寸实在不像是成人使用的，但我也不记得有哪个小孩子戴着这样的礼帽。
EN: It's too small to belong to one of the adults, but I don't remember seeing any chilld wearing a top hat like this.

CN: 校猫？那就难怪了，刚刚我的猫咪人格出现了一段时间。
EN: School Cat? No wonder my cat persona emerged earlier...

CN: 然后把对方的帽子抢走了……她似乎很喜欢这顶帽子。
EN: Then she snatched the other's hat... It seems she liked this hat a lot.

CN: 啊，真是抱歉，我又给大家添麻烦了。
EN: I'm sorry... I seem to have caused trouble for everyone again.

CN: 我会去把帽子送回，顺便送些小鱼干补偿那位校猫吧。
EN: I'll go return the hat and bring some dried fish as an apology to the cat.

CN: 比起鱼干，那位校猫或许更喜欢银芯碎片这种东西……
EN: Instead of dried fish, maybe bring something like Silver fragments...

CN: 比起鱼干，那位校猫或许更喜欢银芯碎片这种东西……
EN: Instead of dried fish, maybe bring something like Silver fragments...

CN: 是这样吗？非常感谢您的帮助，我会努力搜集一下的！
EN: Is that so? Thank you very much for your help! I'll go look for some!

CN: ？你不会全忘光了吧？
EN: ? Did you forget again?

CN: ？你不会全忘光了吧？
EN: ? Did you forget again?

CN: 但我看到了里面的聊天记录，我之前貌似用过它，可我现在忘了要怎么用。
EN: But I saw the chat logs. I think I've used it before, but I don't remember how to use it now...

CN: 那你现在是怎么用的？！
EN: Then how are you using it now?!

CN: 那你现在是怎么用的？！
EN: Then how are you using it now?!

CN: 你别笑我害怕！
EN: Stop laughing! This is serious!

CN: 你别笑我害怕！
EN: Stop laughing! This is serious!

CN: 我把它拆开又装了回去，就大概明白了使用方法。
EN: I took it apart and put it back together, so I kinda figured out how to use it...

CN: 虽然里面的驱动原理很复杂，我还没有弄懂，可能需要多研究一下。
EN: ...Although it's a very complex device, so I haven't fully understood it yet. I'll need to do some more research first.

CN: 你别研究！这不重要，要是报废了很贵的！
EN: Stop researching it! You don't need to know THAT much about it! It's too expensive for you to be messing with it!

CN: 你别研究！这不重要，要是报废了很贵的！
EN: Stop researching it! You don't need to know THAT much about it! It's too expensive for you to be messing with it!

CN: 好吧，所以这个盒子是做什么用的呢？
EN: Then tell me what this box is supposed to do.

CN: 这是校方发给你们的通讯器。
EN: It's a communicator the school gave you.

CN: 这是校方发给你们的通讯器，用来互相远程联络的，遇到危险的时候也可以用它求助。
EN: It's a communicator the school gave you. It'll let you communicate with other people remotely, or used to call for help if you're in danger.

CN: 你真的记得我是谁？
EN: Do you actually remember who I am?

CN: 你真的记得我是谁？
EN: Do you actually remember who I am?

CN: 我记得啊，我答应过你不会忘记的。
EN: Of course I do. I promised I would never forget you!

CN: 你是%player%，你是我的朋友！
EN: You're my friend, %player%!

CN: 守密人%sirormadam%，许久不见，冒昧打扰。
EN: Hello Keeper%sirormadam%. Sorry to bother you after all this time.

CN: 近日我意外得到了两尾漂亮的红色金鱼。
EN: I unexpected obtained two beautiful red goldfish.

CN: 幸运的是，经过我的照料，它们成功产下了不少鱼卵，现在已经孵化成了许许多多的小鱼。
EN: Fortunately, under my care, they successfully laid many eggs. Those eggs have hatched into countless little fish.

CN: 那真不错啊，我记得你很喜欢鱼吧。
EN: That's great. If I recall correctly, you love fish right?

CN: 那真不错啊，我记得你很喜欢鱼吧。
EN: That's great. If I recall correctly, you love fish right?

CN: 是的，我对水底的世界有着发自内心的依恋。
EN: Indeed. I have a profound attachment to the underwater world.

CN: 不好意思，话题扯远了，我是想问问您，有没有兴趣养一些小金鱼？
EN: Sorry, I got sidetracked. I wanted to ask if you would be willing to take care of some of the goldfish.

CN: 它们在水中摆动尾鳍的样子非常可爱，如果莉莉那孩子见了应该也会喜欢的。
EN: The way they wag their tail fins in the water is so cute. I think Lily would love them.

CN: 好啊！可以把它们摆在我和莉莉的房间。
EN: Sure! We can put some in both of our rooms.

CN: 好啊！可以把它们摆在我和莉莉的房间。
EN: Sure! We can put some in both of our rooms.

CN: 那太好了，我会挑一个您方便的时间前来拜访的。
EN: That's great. I'll drop by at a convenient time.

CN: 请暂时对莉莉保密吧，我想给她一个惊喜。
EN: Oh, and let's keep it a secret from Lily for now. I want to surprise her.

CN: 守密人，关于最近我的调查员训练课的改进计划，你有什么建议吗？
EN: Keeper, do you have any suggestions for improving my recent investigator training courses?

CN: 建议就是训练得很好，下次不要练了……
EN: My suggestion: Training was great! There's no need for further training...

CN: 建议就是训练得很好，下次不要练了……
EN: My suggestion: Training was great! There's no need for further training...

CN: 是说训练内容很让人抗拒吗？
EN: Was the training too difficult?

CN: 开玩笑的，主要是体能训练的内容太枯燥了，实在没有什么动力……
EN: Just kidding. I just find the training too boring is all. I don't have any motivation to do it...

CN: 开玩笑的，主要是体能训练的内容太枯燥了，实在没有什么动力……
EN: Just kidding. I just find the training too boring is all. I don't have any motivation to do it...

CN: 嗯，我了解了，看来关键还是兴趣问题。
EN: I see. It seems the main issue is about interest.

CN: 关于这点，我有一个主意，如果我们在训练中中融入军犬配合，大家会不会更有动力呢？
EN: With this in mind, I had an idea. Would people be more motivated if we integrated miltary dogs into the training routine?

CN: 是的，其实这在军队中也是一种常用的方法，士兵的情绪会因为军犬的陪伴而大大舒缓。
EN: Yes. It's actually a commonly used method in the military. Soldiers tend to feel better when accompanied by a dog.

CN: 有毛绒绒的狗狗陪着，的确很幸福！
EN: Having a fluffy dog by my side would certainly motivate me!

CN: 有毛绒绒的狗狗陪着，的确很幸福！
EN: Having a fluffy dog by my side would certainly motivate me!

CN: 而且经过训练的军犬还能出色地辅助士兵完成很多任务，这一点能否运用在调查员任务中也可以进一步展开尝试。
EN: Moreover, well-trained military dogs can greatly assist soldiers in various tasks. Perhaps we can consider adding this to investigator missions.

CN: 真厉害啊，狗狗们。
EN: Dogs... That would be nice...

CN: 真厉害啊，狗狗们。
EN: Dogs... That would be nice...

CN: 没错，所以这样的话，你会更愿意来上训练课了吗？
EN: I take it this would make you more willing to come to training classes?

CN: 艾尔瓦教官！我愿意！
EN: Absolutely, Instructor Alva!

CN: 艾尔瓦教官！我愿意！
EN: Absolutely, Instructor Alva!

CN: 那个，守密人，请问你下次出任务的时候会经过市区吗？
EN: Excuse me, Keeper. Will you be passing through the downtown area on your next mission?

CN: 嗯……就是，如果你什么时候会经过市区，刚好有时间、又顺路的话，能不能帮我带一些新的线团回来呢？
EN: Mm... If you happen to be in the area and have some time, and it's not too much trouble, could you bring me some new yarn?

CN: 是线团不够了吗？我会记住的，你想要什么颜色的？
EN: You're running out of yarn? I'll go get some more then. What color do you want?

CN: 是线团不够了吗？我会记住的，你想要什么颜色的？
EN: You're running out of yarn? I'll go get some more then. What color do you want?

CN: 或者我带你去商店买些新衣服吧！叫上詹金和莉莉一起。
EN: Or better yet, what if we just go shopping for new clothes? We can even bring Jenkin and Lily with us.

CN: 不，不用了！我的衣服都还能穿呢，那太浪费了……
EN: No, no! It's fine! My clothes are still wearable. It would be such a waste...

CN: 怎么会浪费呢？艾继丝，你不用这样小心，我们都很乐意满足你的愿望。
EN: How could it be a waste, Aigis? There's no need to be so frugal. We're all more than happy to fulfill your wishes.

CN: 弥萨格的日常经费也很足够，没有人会再丢下你了，知道吗？
EN: Mythag's daily allowance is more than sufficient. No one will abandon you again, understand?

CN: 好。
EN: Okay.

CN: 好，那我就把每个颜色的线团都买些回来，再买一些布料和丝带怎么样？
EN: Okay then, I'll buy you lots of yarn in every color. I'll even get some fabric and ribbons. How does that sound?

CN: 嗯！
EN: Mm!

CN: 上次你们不是说，洁牙剂不是那个圆圆小盒子里的，而是一条长长的。
EN: Didn't you say that toothpaste comes from the long tube and not the little box?

CN: 为什么我用了长长的那条，现在嘴里这么苦！又辣又苦！！
EN: I used the long tube and now my mouth is on fire! It's so spicy and bitter!!

CN: 呃……按理说不应该是这个味道。
EN: Uh... The toothpaste shouldn't taste like that.

CN: 呃……按理说不应该是这个味道。
EN: Uh... The toothpaste shouldn't taste like that.

CN: 等等，你说的长长的一条，是什么颜色的？
EN: Hold on... What color is the long tube that you used?

CN: 蓝色的，怎么了？
EN: Blue, why?

CN: 那是洗脸用的，洁牙剂是绿色的……
EN: ...That tube is for washing your face. The toothpaste is in the green tube...

CN: 那是洗脸用的，洁牙剂是绿色的……
EN: ...That tube is for washing your face. The toothpaste is in the green tube...

CN: 什么，为什么没人告诉我这件事，是不是你们故意的？！
EN: What?! Why didn't anyone tell me? Are you kidding me?!

CN: 有没有可能上面写着标签呢？
EN: Didn't you read the label?

CN: 有没有可能上面写着标签呢？
EN: Didn't you read the label?

CN: 什么标签？我看不懂。
EN: The label? I can't read it.

CN: 你的基础语言课完全没听吗？？
EN: Can't re—Are you just ignoring your basic language class?!

CN: 你的基础语言课完全没听吗？？
EN: Can't re—Are you just ignoring your basic language class?!

CN: 啊啊啊烦死了！我堂堂迷宫之主，为什么要学习！
EN: Argh, this is all so annoying! Why does the master of the maze have to study!

CN: 快给我找几个奴隶来伺候我！
EN: Hurry up and find me some slaves to attend to me!

CN: 醒醒，罗马亡了。
EN: Wake up princess. Rome's long gone.

CN: 醒醒，罗马亡了。
EN: Wake up princess. Rome's long gone.

CN: 现在是法制社会。
EN: Our society doesn't have rulers and slaves anymore!

CN: 现在是法制社会。
EN: Our society doesn't have rulers and slaves anymore!

CN: 我不管，找不到的话，你就自己来伺候我吧！
EN: I don't care! If you can't bring me anyone, then you should serve me!

CN: 那你还是继续用洁面剂刷牙吧。
EN: Then I guess you should keep using soap to brush your teeth.

CN: 那你还是继续用洁面剂刷牙吧。
EN: Then I guess you should keep using soap to brush your teeth.

CN: 我要把你丢进迷宫里喂子嗣！！！
EN: I'll throw you into the maze to feed my babies!!!

CN: 守密人，为什么我们上次从海边带回来的伙伴不动了……
EN: Keeper, why isn't the friend we brought back from the beach moving...

CN: 伙伴是生病了吗？还是不高兴了……
EN: Is my friend sick or unhappy...?

CN: 守密人能不能帮帮伙伴？
EN: Keeper... help...

CN: 嗯……伙伴应该是想大海了。
EN: Mm... Maybe your friend misses the sea?

CN: 嗯……伙伴应该是想大海了。
EN: Mm... Maybe your friend misses the sea?

CN: 它从大海里来，我们一起去把它送回大海好不好？
EN: Since they came from the sea, maybe we should return them back home?

CN: 原来是这样吗……我明白的，伙伴想家了。
EN: I see... my friend is feeling homesick...

CN: 奥瑞塔也想大海，但奥瑞塔也喜欢学校，奥瑞塔现在有两个家。
EN: Aurita misses the sea too, but... Aurita also loves school! Aurita has two homes!

CN: 走吧！我们去送伙伴回家！然后再一起回来，回学校的家！
EN: OK, let's go! Let's send our friend back home! Then we can return together, back to our home!

CN: 守密人，之前我提到的那个偏方……
EN: Keeper, about that remedy I mentioned earlier...

CN: 失败了？没关系，这很正常，毕竟是来路不明的东西。
EN: Did it fail? That's okay. I expected it would considering its dubious origin.

CN: 好像有些效果。
EN: Actually, it seems to be working.

CN: 呃？？是什么效果？你觉醒成功了？
EN: Wait, what? It's working? Have you fully awakened?

CN: 呃？？是什么效果？你觉醒成功了？
EN: Wait, what? It's working? Have you fully awakened?

CN: 那倒没有，我攒了一阵钱，刚刚开始尝试不久。
EN: Not yet, I've been saving up the bottles for a while. I've only just started using them...

CN: 但我能感受到血脉的躁动，每天我的胸口都有力量在奔涌的感觉，甚至晚上经常会流鼻血。
EN: ...but I can feel my blood boiling! Every day, I can feel the power surging within me! I've also been having nosebleeds at night.

CN: 流鼻血？你怕不是生病了吧，要不先去校医室看看？
EN: Boiling blood? Nosebleeds? It sounds like you're sick. You should go get checked out at the infirmary...

CN: 流鼻血？你怕不是生病了吧，要不先去校医室看看？
EN: Boiling blood? Nosebleeds? It sounds like you're sick. You should go get checked out at the infirmary...

CN: 守密人，你还是这样容易嫉妒我，这分明是血脉开始变强的体现。
EN: Ahh, Keeper, you truly are jealous of me. This is clearly a sign of my bloodline growing stronger.

CN: 只要等我的身体承受住这样的蜕变，我一定会获得无上的力量的。
EN: As long as my body can withstand these trials, I will surely attain supreme power.

CN: 只是最近鼻血流得太多，弄坏了好多件衣服，只剩下身上最后这一件了。
EN: But with all of the nosebleeds I've had, I've soiled and ruined most of my clothes. What I'm currently wearing is all that's left.

CN: 守密人，能不能给我五十，我去买几件新衣服。
EN: So, Keeper. I need fifty to buy some new clothes.

CN: 搞了半天你还是来借钱的啊？！！
EN: So you've come to borrow money after all?!

CN: 搞了半天你还是来借钱的啊？！！
EN: So you've come to borrow money after all?!

CN: 所以我桌子上这本写完的作业是你拿来的？
EN: So you're the one that brought this finished homework?

CN: 所以我桌子上这本写完的作业是你拿来的？
EN: So you're the one that brought this finished homework?

CN: 是的，您的愿望是希望一觉醒来作业就已经完成了。
EN: Yes. Thy wish was to wake up and find your assignments already completed.

CN: 我好像是说过这种话……但这本作业上写着拉蒙娜的名字！！
EN: Yes, I did say that, but... this homework has Ramona's name on it!!

CN: 我好像是说过这种话……但这本作业上写着拉蒙娜的名字！！
EN: Yes, I did say that, but... this homework has Ramona's name on it!!

CN: 不用客气，我调查过，拉蒙娜是目前作业成绩最好的。
EN: You're welcome. After investigating, I discovered Ramona currently has the best homework grades.

CN: 这是客气的问题吗？！
EN: What do you mean "you're welcome"?!

CN: 这是客气的问题吗？！
EN: What do you mean "you're welcome"?!

CN: 等等，我自己原来的那本作业呢？
EN: Wait, where's my homework ?

CN: 为了保持作业的数量不变，我已经把它放到拉蒙娜那里了。
EN: I exchanged it with Ramona's so the number of assignments are consistent.

CN: 放心，她没有发现。
EN: Don't worry. She didn't notice.

CN: 放心，她肯定发现了……
EN: Don't worry? She'll definitely notice!

CN: 放心，她肯定发现了……
EN: Don't worry? She'll definitely notice!

CN: 坏了，怎么有人来敲门了……
EN: ...Someone's knocking on my door...

CN: 希莱斯特，我要重新许愿，快来救我！！！
EN: Celeste! Save me! I wish for you to save me!

CN: 好的，您的愿望我已知晓，我马上来。
EN: I have heard thy wish. I shall head there immediately.

CN: 算了，来不及了，还是先帮我联系医务室吧！！！
EN: Forget it, it's too late! Call the infirmary for me!!!

CN: 算了，来不及了，还是先帮我联系医务室吧！！！
EN: Forget it, it's too late! Call the infirmary for me!!!

CN: 没错。
EN: That's right.

CN: 没错，卡茜亚，有人和我举报昨天你在学校食堂进行临时魔术表演之后，食堂仓库的三只母鸡和二十个鸡蛋都消失了。
EN: That's right. Casiah, someone reported that after your impromptu magic show in the school cafeteria yesterday, three hens and twenty eggs went missing from the storage.

CN: 什么？还有这样的事，卡茜亚不知道呀。
EN: Whaaat~? How could that have happened? Casiah is truly perplexed.

CN: 哎呀，好像是哦，那几只鸡可能自己飞走了吧？
EN: Ah, I suppose that DID happen... Maybe those chickens flew away on their own?

CN: 或许它们迷失在了无尽的帽子世界里，真是太可怜了！
EN: Or maybe they're stuck somewhere in the mysterious hat dimension! How sad...

CN: 如果你再不考虑说实话的话……
EN: Casiah, if you keep lying...

CN: 如果你再不考虑说实话的话，我就要联系达芙黛尔女士来管理一下她的员工了。
EN: Casiah, if you keep lying, I'll tell Lady Daffodil that her employee is stealing Mythag property.

CN: 好吧好吧，真是没有幽默感！
EN: Geez, alright! You and your lacking sense of humor!

CN: 因为卡茜亚最近在研究“母爱”这种感情，可是学校的唤醒体里能参考的人太少啦！
EN: Casiah has been researching "motherly love" recently, but there aren't enough references among the Awakened!

CN: 所以卡茜亚想到了好办法，先从动物身上开始研究！这样就容易多啦！
EN: So Casiah had a great idea: let's research animals! That's much easier!

CN: ……所以那几只鸡现在在哪里？
EN: ...So where are the chickens now?

CN: ……所以那几只鸡现在在哪里？
EN: ...So where are the chickens now?

CN: 在卡茜亚的房间，现在已经有很多小鸡孵出来了！每天都非常热闹呢！
EN: In Casiah's room, where many newly hatched chicks now roam free! My room has become very lively!

CN: 给我好好还给食堂啊！！
EN: Return those hens to the cafeteria already!!

CN: 给我好好还给食堂啊！！
EN: Return those hens to the cafeteria already!!

CN: 咦，你居然要残忍地拆散这些母子，真是太冷酷了！你这个没有母爱的人！
EN: How cruel you are Keeper! Wishing to seperate these chicks from their mothers! Have you forgotten about maternal love?!

CN: 我到底为什么要对鸡有母爱啊！
EN: I'm not going to feel maternal love towards a bunch of chickens!

CN: 我到底为什么要对鸡有母爱啊！
EN: I'm not going to feel maternal love towards a bunch of chickens!

CN: 以及真是唯独不想被你说冷酷啊！
EN: And I won't be called cold-hearted by someone like you!

CN: 以及真是唯独不想被你说冷酷啊！
EN: And I won't be called cold-hearted by someone like you!

CN: 录音时朵尔教授还提到，校方制作出了一款新型的录音机，体型小巧，音质细腻，甚至可以在出任务时随身携带，有录音和播放的功能。
EN: During the recording session, Professor Doll also mentioned that the school had developed a new type of tape recorder. It's small and portable for missions, has clear audio, and features both recording and playback functions.

CN: 我看到后就想到了你，如果需要的话，我可以为你录制你想听的乐曲。
EN: When I saw it, I thought of you. If you'd like, I can make a recording of the music you like to listen to.

CN: 这样即使有时我不在你的身边，也不会担心没有音乐来抚慰你的灵魂。
EN: That way, even when I'm not by your side, you need not worry about lacking music to soothe your soul.

CN: 哈姆林……我好感动！
EN: Hameln... I'm so moved!

CN: 哈姆林……我好感动！
EN: Hameln... I'm so moved!

CN: 这都是我应尽的职责，那么，有什么想听的吗？
EN: It's simply fulfilling my duty. Well then, is there anything you wish to listen to?

CN: 有助睡眠的音乐
EN: Relaxing music.

CN: 说起来，每次听你吹奏摇篮曲的时候，我都会睡得很好。
EN: Speaking of which, I always sleep well whenever you perform a lullaby.

CN: 这首曲子有什么特别的吗？
EN: What's makes it so special?

CN: 要这一首吗？我明白了。
EN: You wish to hear that style? Understood.

CN: 如果非要说特别之处，大概是充满了我守护你的心情吧。
EN: If I must specify what’s special about it, it must be because it’s brimming with my need to protect you.

CN: 帮助起床的音乐
EN: Energetic music.

CN: 其实我一直都有点起床困难，如果有那种令人振奋的音乐，起床应该会容易一些吧！
EN: Actually, I’ve always had a bit of trouble getting up. If I had some rousing music, it would probable be easier to get out of bed!

CN: 令人振奋吗？我明白了。
EN: Rousing music? Understood.

CN: 虽然我觉得充足良好的睡眠才是更重要的，但毕竟你肩负了如此多的责任，忙碌也是在所难免。
EN: Even though I think it’s more important to get quality sleep, you shoulder such numerous burdens that business is unavoidable.

CN: 希望这首进行曲能够带给你力量。
EN: May this march lend you strength!

CN: 守密人！请问我刚刚是不是去给你送了饼干？
EN: Keeper! Did I just bring you some cookies?

CN: 呃，没错？
EN: Uh, yeah?

CN: 呃，没错？我刚刚吃完，味道很不错，你的手艺真是越来越好了。
EN: Uh, yeah? I just finished eating them, they were delicious. You've gotten really good at baking.

CN: 啊！天呐！我来就是想告诉你千万不要吃那些饼干！那些饼干不是我做的！
EN: Oh no! I wanted to tell you to NOT eat those cookies! I didn't make them!

CN: 什么？不是你做的？
EN: Wait, what? You didn't make them?

CN: 什么？不是你做的？
EN: Wait, what? You didn't make them?

CN: 是的，刚刚给你送饼干的是我另一个新诞生的人格，她非常喜欢恶作剧……
EN: Yes! The one that made those cookies is one of my new personalities. She loves playing pranks...

CN: 我模糊地记得她好像在做饼干的时候加入了什么东西……总之你现在有没有哪里不舒服？
EN: I think she added something to the cookies while she made them... Are you alright?

CN: 你这么一说，我突然感觉全身都不舒服了……
EN: Now that you mention it, I'm feeling a sudden sense of dread...

CN: 你这么一说，我突然感觉全身都不舒服了……
EN: Now that you mention it, I'm feeling a sudden sense of dread...

CN: 她到底放了什么，总不会是致命毒药吧？？
EN: What did she add? It's not poison, is it?!

CN: 应该不会的！她只是喜欢恶作剧，并没有那么邪恶。
EN: I don't think she'd go that far! She just likes to prank people.

CN: 怎么办，我又给你添麻烦了，我，我现在去联系茜尔维亚女士！
EN: What should I do? I've troubled you again. I'll contact Ms. Sylvia right away!

CN: 等等，慢着，不用了……
EN: Wait, don't...

CN: 等等，慢着，不用了……我知道她放的是什么了……
EN: Wait, don't... I think I figured out what she added...

CN: 是泻药……
EN: The thing she added...

CN: 是泻药……不说了……我要赶紧去一下厕所……
EN: The thing she added... it was a laxative. I'll be going to the bathroom now.

CN: 我房间的纸可能不够了，一会儿记得给我送点纸……
EN: I might run out of paper, so please bring me some later...

CN: 好，好的，我会的！对不起！！
EN: I will, I'll do it! I'm sorry!!

CN: 这一阵实行的军犬陪同训练效果超乎我的想象。
EN: It seems the addition of military dogs to my training have far exceeded my expectations.

CN: 甚至有原本不参与体能训练的同学也来找我报名上课，大家的热情真是让我惊讶。
EN: Even students who didn't originally participate in physical training are signing up for my classes. I'm really surprised by everyone's enthusiasm.

CN: 毕竟毛绒绒的小狗没有人能够拒绝！！！
EN: Nobody could possibly resist the charm of fluffy puppies!!!

CN: 毕竟毛绒绒的小狗没有人能够拒绝！！！
EN: Nobody could possibly resist the charm of fluffy puppies!!!

CN: 的确，为了让小狗和同学们培养出更多配合的默契，我选用的都是尚未成年的幼犬。
EN: Indeed. I selected puppies in order to foster better teamwork among the students.

CN: 虽然我和大家一样喜欢这些小家伙们，但幼犬需要的照顾和教导的确要比成年犬多得多。
EN: While I do adore these little ones as much as my students do, they do require more care and training than adult dogs.

CN: 现在报名人数增加，相应的小狗数量也要增加，还真让我有些招架不来。
EN: With the increased number of students enrolling in my class, the number of puppies needed has also increased. It's become difficult for me to handle them all myself.

CN: 这太简单了。
EN: An easily solved problem!

CN: 这太简单了，只要艾尔瓦教官一声令下，保证有更多的人愿意报名来照顾小狗，到时候只怕小狗都不够分。
EN: An easily solved problem! If Instructor Alva simply asks for some assistance, plenty of people will sign up to take care of the puppies. In fact, there might be more volunteers then puppies!

CN: 你是说招募一些志愿者吗？确实是好主意。
EN: Recruiting volunteers? That's a good idea.

CN: 那么我一会就去找诃勒特院长申请这件事，顺利的话，同学们也可以见到更多的小狗了。
EN: I'll make a request to Dean Czort to sign off on this. If all goes well, the students will also be able to see more puppies.

CN: 守密人，请问……您什么时候有时间，能够与我见一次面呢？
EN: Keeper, if it's OK... would you have time to meet with me?

CN: 啊，当然！如果您很忙的话，能够把贴身的衣物借给我也是可以的！
EN: Oh, but..! If you're too busy, lending me your underwear would work too!

CN: 贴身衣物？这是要做什么吗？
EN: Underwear? Why do you need that?

CN: 贴身衣物？这是要做什么吗？
EN: Underwear? Why do you need that?

CN: 是，是这样的，最近我和梅森姐姐学会了织毛线，我给莉莉和詹金织了围巾和帽子。
EN: Yes, well... Recently, I've been learning to knit with Sister Mason. So far I've made scarves and hats for Lily and Jenkin.

CN: 哇，真厉害呀！
EN: Wow, that's impressive!

CN: 哇，真厉害呀！
EN: Wow, that's impressive!

CN: 没有，都是很简单的……
EN: No, it's nothing special...

CN: 不过现在我已经很熟练了，可以织一些更难的东西，所以想给守密人织一件毛衣！
EN: But now I'm skilled enough to knit more complex things, so I want to knit a sweater for you, Keeper!

CN: 毛衣的话，我需要给守密人量一下尺寸，当然，如果守密人不需要的话就不用麻烦了！
EN: Before I knit the sweater, I need your measurements. Oh, but if you don't want it, then you don't have to!

CN: 怎么会呢？小艾继丝想着我，我高兴还来不及。
EN: How could that be the case? I'm happy that Aigis is thinking about me.

CN: 怎么会呢？小艾继丝想着我，我高兴还来不及。
EN: How could that be the case? I'm happy that Aigis is thinking about me.

CN: 我觉得红色或者白色的毛衣都很好看，守密人想要什么颜色的呢？
EN: I think both red or white sweaters would look good on you. Which color do you want, Keeper?

CN: 好的，艾继丝记住了！我会努力的！
EN: OK, Aigis will remember! I'll do my best!

CN: 喂！快来帮我！我被被子缠住了！
EN: Hey! Help me! I'm tangled up in the blanket!

CN: ？你被什么？？
EN: ? I'm sorry, what??

CN: ？你被什么？？
EN: ? I'm sorry, what??

CN: 还不是都怪你们不给我配奴隶！！谁知道这个破被单为什么这么难换啊！
EN: This is all your fault for not assigning me slaves!! Why the hell is this damn bedsheet so difficult to change?!

CN: 怎么塞都塞不明白，气得我跟被子打了起来！
EN: I coudn't figure out how to fold it, so I started fighting with the blanket!

CN: 愣着干什么，还不快过来救我！我出不来了！
EN: Well?! Don't just ... me, hurry up and save me! I can't get out!

CN: 有时候很疑惑你这种人是怎么活到这么大的。
EN: I'm honestly impressed that someone like you has managed to survive this long.

CN: 有时候很疑惑你这种人是怎么活到这么大的。
EN: I'm honestly impressed that someone like you has managed to survive this long.

CN: 明明这些都是奴隶该做的工作，怎么会这么困难……
EN: These menial tasks are for slaves to do! Why are they so difficult...?

CN: 以前那些奴隶每天都在做这些吗？不可能，他们是怎么做到的？
EN: Did those slaves really do this every day? That's impossible! How did they do it?

CN: 这已经算最简单的家务了，你真是脱离生活太久了。
EN: This is one of the easiest chores someone could do. You're completely out of touch with normal day to day life.

CN: 这已经算最简单的家务了，你真是脱离生活太久了。
EN: This is one of the easiest chores someone could do. You're completely out of touch with normal day to day life.

CN: 哼……那我以后对奴隶温柔一点就是了，你快给我找些勤劳的奴隶来！
EN: Hmph... I suppose I'll treat my future slaves better. Now go find me some hard working ones!

CN: 都说了罗马亡了啊！
EN: How many times do I have to tell you that Rome is long gone!

CN: 都说了罗马亡了啊！
EN: How many times do I have to tell you that Rome is long gone!

CN: 现在是法制社会，你做梦吧！
EN: There aren't any slaves to serve you in modern day society!

CN: 现在是法制社会，你做梦吧！
EN: There aren't any slaves to serve you in modern day society!

CN: 我不管！我不管啊啊啊啊，要我每天做这些家务不如让我去死！！
EN: I don't care, I don't care, I don't care! I'd rather die than be forced to do these chores every day!

CN: 呵呵，不止家务，还有作业呢。
EN: Both chores and homework, huh?

CN: 呵呵，不止家务，还有作业呢。
EN: Both chores and homework, huh?

CN: 我要把你丢进迷宫喂子嗣！！！！
EN: I'll throw you into the maze to feed my babies!!!

CN: 怎么搞的？？
EN: What happened??

CN: 怎么搞的？？
EN: What happened??

CN: 刚刚奥瑞塔想和伙伴们一起玩，于是跳进了鱼缸里，结果，哗啦——
EN: So Aurita wanted to play with her friends! So I jumped into the fish tank—splash—

CN: 奥瑞塔太大，鱼缸太小，里面的水就全都挤出来啦！
EN: But Aurita is too big! And the tank is too small! So all the water in the tank splashed out!

CN: 呃，是你能做出来的事，没事，我这就来。
EN: Well, that's about what I suspected. Don't worry, I'm on my way.

CN: 呃，是你能做出来的事，没事，我这就来。
EN: Well, that's about what I suspected. Don't worry, I'm on my way.

CN: 唉，奥瑞塔想要一个大大的鱼缸，超级大，有整个房间那么大！
EN: Mm... Aurita wishes she had a big fish tank! A SUPER big one, as big as my room!

CN: 这样奥瑞塔和伙伴们就可以每天都在一起玩了！
EN: That way, Aurita and her friends can play together every day!

CN: 梦想很美好，然而学校并没有经费建一个水族馆啊！
EN: It's a nice wish, but the school can't afford to build an aquarium!

CN: 梦想很美好，然而学校并没有经费建一个水族馆啊！
EN: It's a nice wish, but the school can't afford to build an aquarium!

CN: 哎——为什么，那半个房间那么大的也可以嘛！
EN: Mm—Even one as big as half a room would work too!

CN: 是，你只是单纯的穷。
EN: Yeah, because you're always poor.

CN: 是，你只是单纯的穷。
EN: Yeah, because you're always poor.

CN: 那就是那个偏方的事？
EN: So Is this about that remedy?

CN: 嗯，我想我的天赋或许就到此为止了……
EN: Well, it seems my journey for power ends here...

CN: 自从服用那个偏方之后，我每天能感觉到血脉的躁动，但觉醒的变化却迟迟没有来。
EN: Ever since I started taking that remedy, my blood boiled every day, but I'm no closer to my Awakening.

CN: 喝那种奇怪的东西能突破就怪了吧……
EN: Like I said before, drinking that "remedy" was unlikely to result in your Awakening...

CN: 喝那种奇怪的东西能突破就怪了吧……
EN: Like I said before, drinking that "remedy" was unlikely to result in your Awakening...

CN: 像我这样没用的人，是否早点放弃，给自己找一个墓穴等死比较好呢？
EN: It seems the only thing left for a useless failure like me would be to crawl into a grave and die...

CN: 也不至于这么极端！！
EN: That's a bit of an extreme conclusion!

CN: 也不至于这么极端！！
EN: That's a bit of an extreme conclusion!

CN: 我一直就觉得吧，这不是你的问题，你是真的被卖你偏方的人骗了，对方只是在利用你迫切的心情。
EN: Listen, it's not your fault. You were decieved and preyed upon by those that sold you that remedy; they took advantage of your desperation.

CN: 你的身体也不是无法承受突破，而是单纯中毒生病了啊！
EN: It's not a matter of you being unable to Awaken; you've been poisoned by quack medicine!

CN: 原来是这样吗？你说的好像有道理。
EN: Is that so? What you're saying does make sense.

CN: 我不是早就在说了吗！！
EN: So now you believe me?!

CN: 我不是早就在说了吗！！
EN: So now you believe me?!

CN: 原来我只是生病了，那么说明我的觉醒还是有希望的。
EN: So I'm just suck? Then there is still hope for me to Awaken!

CN: 嗯嗯……没错没错，所以你只要好好治病就好了。
EN: Yes, yes, that's right. So just relax and focus on getting better.

CN: 嗯嗯……没错没错，所以你只要好好治病就好了。
EN: Yes, yes, that's right. So just relax and focus on getting better.

CN: 我明白了，谢谢你，守密人。
EN: I understand. Thank you, Keeper.

CN: 所以……能给我五十去看病吗？
EN: So. Can you lend me fifty so I can see a doctor?

CN: 怎么最后还是要借钱啊！！！
EN: So it's still about borrowing money after all!!!

CN: 怎么最后还是要借钱啊！！！
EN: So it's still about borrowing money after all!!!

CN: 守密人，为什么弥萨格的大家都不来找我许愿了呢？
EN: Keeper, why doesn't anyone from Mythag ask me to fulfill their wishes anymore?

CN: 嗯……可能因为弥萨格的大家都是务实派吧。
EN: Mm... I suppose it's because people at Mythag are pragmatic.

CN: 嗯……可能因为弥萨格的大家都是务实派吧。
EN: Mm... I suppose it's because people at Mythag are pragmatic.

CN: 每天面对无数危险，精神已经非常稳定，不会把事情寄托于许愿来解决了。
EN: Having faced countless dangers every day, their spirits have become resillient enough to not rely on wishing to save them.

CN: 没有没有！其实吧，大家也不是完全不相信这些啦。
EN: No, no! It's not like everyone has completely stopped wishing for things.

CN: 没有没有！其实吧，大家也不是完全不相信这些啦。
EN: No, no! It's not like everyone has completely stopped wishing for things.

CN: 如果是那种比较抽象的、长远的愿望，大家还是很热衷凑热闹许个愿的。
EN: It's moreso that their wishes have become more abstract; longterm.

CN: 我不太明白，什么是抽象的、长远的愿望？
EN: I don't understand. What do you mean by abstract?

CN: 就比如，逢考必过啦，增长财运啦，甜甜恋爱啦之类的。
EN: Things like passing exams, improving one's wealth, experiencing a sweet romance...

CN: 就比如，逢考必过啦，增长财运啦，甜甜恋爱啦之类的。
EN: Things like passing exams, improving one's wealth, experiencing a sweet romance...

CN: 与其说是许愿，更像是大家希望获得一份好运和祝福吧。
EN: Instead of asking for it to be directly fulfilled, people want something to dream about; to look forward to.

CN: 愿望这种东西，哪怕不能立刻实现，留在心中也是一份安慰和期待。
EN: Even if their wishes don't immediately come true, the very act of wishing for something can bring comfort to them.

CN: 我好像明白了，明天开始我就去学校的喷泉里为大家送上祝福吧。
EN: I think I understand now. Starting tomorrow, I will give everyone my blessings at the school's fountain.

CN: 虽然好像有道理，但感觉还是很奇怪啊！
EN: I get the logic, but it's a little strange!

CN: 虽然好像有道理，但感觉还是很奇怪啊！
EN: I get the logic, but it's a little strange!

CN: 当当，卡茜亚魔术小课堂开课啦！
EN: Ta-da~! Casiah's magic class is now in session!

CN: 你又要搞什么？？
EN: What are you up to now??

CN: 你又要搞什么？？
EN: What are you up to now??

CN: 什么嘛，这次我可是受学校邀请，认真给大家上课的！
EN: What? I'm serious! The school invited me to give a lecture!

CN: 朵尔告诉我，试着当一次老师可以体验教育和传承的感觉。
EN: Doll told me that teaching would let me "experience the feeling of education and legacy."

CN: 虽然有点难以理解那种东西，但现在开始请叫我卡茜亚老师吧！
EN: I don't really get it, but regardless, please call me Professor Casiah!

CN: 呃，卡茜亚……老师。比起你我更难以理解啊！！
EN: Uh, Casi—Professor Casiah... I'm the one that doesn't get how you can teach at all!!

CN: 呃，卡茜亚……老师。比起你我更难以理解啊！！
EN: Uh, Casi—Professor Casiah... I'm the one that doesn't get how you can teach at all!!

CN: 怎么了？卡茜亚老师的魔术手法可是神奇的不传之秘！想要隔空取物、隔山打牛、穿墙偷窃……
EN: What? Professor Casiah can teach lots of incredible secrets! I could teach you how to juggle, how to pierce through objects, or to steal an object inside a safe...

CN: 后面的东西越来越不对了吧！！
EN: These subjects are getting increasingly weird, aren't they?!

CN: 后面的东西越来越不对了吧！！
EN: These subjects are getting increasingly weird, aren't they?!

CN: ……这些都学不到！
EN: ...but I won't!

CN: 那你说出来干什么？！
EN: Then why did you bother listing them?!

CN: 那你说出来干什么？！
EN: Then why did you bother listing them?!

CN: 哎呀，这些都是卡茜亚老师的独门绝活，你们当然是学不会的啦。
EN: Well, those are Professor Casiah's exclusive skills. Of course you can't learn them!

CN: 不过卡茜亚老师可以教你们让双手变得灵巧的方法，这样以后遇到挣不脱的绳子、打不开的锁，也能掌握溜门撬锁、顺手牵羊的技术！
EN: But what Professor Casiah CAN teach you is how to make your hands nimble. That way, when you're bound by a rope that can't be untied or stumble on a lock that can't be opened, you'll be able to showcase your ability to take advantage of opportunities!

CN: 果然还是在教奇怪的东西啊！！
EN: So you're still set on teaching weird things!

CN: 果然还是在教奇怪的东西啊！！
EN: So you're still set on teaching weird things!

CN: 奇怪的词不要乱用啊！！
EN: Enough with these weird examples already!!

CN: 奇怪的词不要乱用啊！！
EN: Enough with these weird examples already!!

CN: 啧，朵尔面对的学生也都这么多事吗？好麻烦，当老师真没意思。
EN: Tsk, does Doll have to deal with students this troublesome all the time? How annoying! Being a teacher sucks!

CN: 虽然朵尔老师确实很辛苦，但唯独不想被你嫌弃啊！
EN: While Ms. Doll does have it tough sometimes, I absolutely will NOT be crticized by the likes of you!

CN: 虽然朵尔老师确实很辛苦，但唯独不想被你嫌弃啊！
EN: While Ms. Doll does have it tough sometimes, I absolutely will NOT be crticized by the likes of you!

CN: %player%%sirormadam%，最近我又创作了一首新的曲子，想请你在闲暇时间来点评一二。
EN: {Male=Mr.,Female=Miss} %player%. I've recently composed a new piece and would like to invite you to give it a listen and critique in your free time.

CN: 你真是太客气了。
EN: You're too kind.

CN: 你真是太客气了，哈姆林，我这种半吊子哪有资格来点评你的作品啊。
EN: You're too kind Hameln, but how can a half-baked amateur like me be qualified to critique your work?

CN: 不，不必妄自菲薄，你的建议是我创作最大的动力。
EN: No, don’t downplay your significance; your suggestions are my greatest source of creative motivation.

CN: 有这么夸张吗？
EN: Really?

CN: 有这么夸张吗？不过，虽然很不好意思说，其实我每次听你新作的曲子都会听睡着……
EN: Really? I'm ashamed to admit this, but I tend to fall asleep when I listen to your new compositions...

CN: 你的曲子是很优美，演奏也无可挑剔，就是每次我都像着了魔一样很快就睡晕过去了，可能我真的没有什么音乐天赋吧。
EN: Your music is hauntingly beautiful and flawlessly performed, yet it casts some sedative magic on me and I fall asleep instantly. Perhaps I truly lack a musical ear.

CN: 不，这正是我想要的。
EN: No, that is exactly what I want.

CN: 能为你带来安眠，正是我的使命与职责。
EN: Being able to bring you restful sleep is my mission and duty.

CN: 不如说，请你具体描述不同曲子为你带来的感受，以及听完后的睡眠质量，入睡的速度和睡眠时长等等。
EN: Rather, please describe to me in detail the feelings that different pieces bring you, as well as your post-listening sleep quality, how long it takes to fall asleep, the duration of your sleep...

CN: 啊，这样的要求确实有些苛刻，是我考虑不周。
EN: Ah, such requests are rather austere. My apologies for being inconsiderate.

CN: 不如下次就让我在你的床前演奏，让我来细致记录你的睡眠吧。
EN: How about next time I play by your bedside and you allow me to observe and record your sleep.

CN: 我希望你的每一次入睡，都有我的守候。
EN: I hope you fall asleep every time under my protection.

CN: 詹金的唤醒，进行得怎么样了？
EN: How is Jenkin's awakening going?

CN: 快要完成了
EN: Almost done.

CN: 学校的材料库已经把她的身体所需物品准备好，现在正在进行唤醒体制作。
EN: The school's material library has prepared everything needed for her Body, and the process of her Awakening is currently happening.

CN: 我们很快，就可以再见到她了！
EN: We'll be able to see her again very soon!

CN: 太好了！太好了……
EN: That's great!

CN: 谢谢你，守密人。谢谢你们……
EN: Thank you, Keeper. Thank you...

CN: 我们应该感谢你，还有詹金。
EN: I should be the one thanking you and Jenkin.

CN: 你和詹金救了我们。
EN: You two saved us.

CN: 她是为了救弥萨格而死，这些都是我们应该做的。
EN: She died for the sake of saving Mythag. Any investigator would do the same.

CN: 校委会已经讨论通过，你们二位，不用再担心流落在外了。
EN: The school committee already discussed and approved of your acts, so you two don't need to worry about being abandoned anymore.

CN: 欢迎加入弥萨格。
EN: Welcome to Mythag, 24.

CN: 我收到了一条消息……
EN: ...Hold on, someone's at my door...

CN: 詹金的唤醒体制作，顺利完成。
EN: Jenkin has successfully Awakened.

CN: 船长，身体一直在衰弱……
EN: Captain, my body has been weakening...

CN: 这恐怕很难，但弥萨格一定会有办法
EN: It might be difficult, but Mythag will surely find a way.

CN: 这恐怕很难，希莱斯特。
EN: It won't be easy, Celeste.

CN: 即使是调查员，链接唤醒体也是一个巨大的负担。
EN: Linking to an Awakaner is a tremendous burden on one's body, even for a trained investigator.

CN: 更何况，埃尔顿船长在这方面，只是一个普通人。
EN: For a layman like Captain Elton, it's even more of a strain.

CN: 他能与你链接这么久，已经是奇迹。
EN: The fact that he's been able to maintain a link with you for this long is already a miracle.

CN: 不过请放心，我一定会帮你们想办法的。
EN: But don't worry, I'll definitely find a way to help both of you.

CN: 弥利亚姆能做到的事情，弥萨格一定也能做到。
EN: If Miryam can do it, Mythag most certainly can too.

CN: 人们向我许愿，但对身边之人，我束手无策……
EN: People make wishes to me, yet I am powerless to help those around me...

CN: 若有机会，请救下船长。
EN: If it is possible, please save the captain.

CN: 我的迷宫已经重新建好了，我按记忆里的样子，在那里修了一整座竞技场！
EN: I have rebuilt my Maze! An entire arena constructed according to my memories!

CN: 你什么时候能改改你的语气……
EN: Will you ever be able to ask instead of order...?

CN: 你那种命令奴隶的语气，什么时候才能改改……
EN: Will you ever be able to ask instead of order...?

CN: 哼，这有什么好改的。
EN: Hmph, why would I bother changing my manner of speaking?

CN: 我已经让了一万步了！现在我都只在迷宫里使唤那些奴隶。
EN: I've already made ten thousand concessions! The only people I get to order around are the slaves in my maze!

CN: 你现在不怕回忆那些事情了？
EN: So you're alright with everything now?

CN: 你现在不怕回忆那些事情了？
EN: So you're alright with everything now?

CN: 那是。有什么好怕的！
EN: Of course. What's there to be afraid of?

CN: 伦蒂尼恩不允许养奴隶，这个野蛮的地方。
EN: As you've reminded me many times, slaves aren't allowed in Londinium. This barbaric land...

CN: 他们在竞技场里打起来的样子，真的跟我以前见过的一模一样！
EN: The way they fight in the arena is exactly how I remember it!

CN: 原来迷宫是用来做这个的……
EN: So that's what the Maze is used for...

CN: 没错没错！可有意思了！
EN: That's right, that's right! It's really exciting!

CN: 快跟我一起去看看！这可是无上的荣耀！
EN: Come on, let's go watch! This is the ultimate honor I can grant you!

CN: 那我把尤乌哈希也一起叫上吧
EN: Then I'll bring Uvhash along.

CN: 倒也不是不行，多了解一下历史也没什么坏处……
EN: Sure, why not? Learning more about history would be nice...

CN: 尤乌哈希应该会很喜欢你的竞技场的，要不顺便把他也一起叫上吧？
EN: Uvhash would probably really like your arena. Why not invite him as well?

CN: 怎么样，守密人，被安迪·约翰逊的舞台布置震撼到了吧！
EN: So, Keeper? Are you amazed by Andy Johnson's stage setup!

CN: 的确很不错！
EN: It was great!

CN: 当大导演真是当上瘾了……
EN: While you did go a big overboard...

CN: 不过，你布置的舞台确实很不错。
EN: ...I must say that the stage you arranged is truly impressive.

CN: 演出的调度也做得很好。
EN: The timing of the performance is also well executed.

CN: 下一部作品就靠你了！
EN: The next project will depend on you!

CN: 那么，下一部的布景和导演，就决定是你了！
EN: The setting and director for the next installment are up to you!

CN: 什么，不包括编剧吗？
EN: What? What about the screenwriter?

CN: 希望这次你们能对表演有所敬畏，不要再拿出来一个什么「女孩从此和妈妈幸福地生活在了一起」之类的东西了！
EN: I hope next time you'll show some respect for the performance and refrain from bringing up something like "the girl lived happily with her mother from then on"!

CN: 奥瑞塔觉得呢？
EN: Well, what do you think?

CN: 奥瑞塔觉得那些是什么？
EN: Well, what do you think?

CN: 唔……奥瑞塔想不起来……
EN: Umm... Aurita can't seem to remember...

CN: 朋友……
EN: Friends...

CN: 那些，都是奥瑞塔的朋友。
EN: Those are all Aurita's friends.

CN: 朋友？奥瑞塔最喜欢朋友了！
EN: Friends? Aurita loves friends the most!

CN: 后来，他们要去一个很远的地方。
EN: But one day, they had to go to a faraway place.

CN: 他们怕奥瑞塔伤心，所以就带走了奥瑞塔与他们的记忆。
EN: Worried that Aurita would be sad when they left, they decided to erase her memories of them.

CN: 但他们依然想要陪伴着奥瑞塔，所以，他们留下了自己的身体。
EN: But they still wished to stay by her side, so they left their bodies behind.

CN: 这些身体变成了小陶偶，留在了奥瑞塔的水宫殿里。
EN: These bodies turned into small clay dolls and were left in Aurita's Water Palace.

CN: ……他们一直都关心、陪伴着奥瑞塔，从来没有改变过。
EN: ...They have always cared for and accompanied you. That has never changed.

CN: 好像听明白了，又好像没有明白……
EN: I think I get it... but I also don't...

CN: 不过，奥瑞塔知道了！水宫殿里的那些，都是奥瑞塔的好朋友。
EN: But! Aurita does know that those in the Water Palace are all good friends of Aurita.

CN: 奥瑞塔会好好照顾他们，每天都找他们一起玩！
EN: So Aurita will take good care of them and play with them every day!

CN: 24，你的人格又切换了……
EN: 24, your personality switched again...

CN: 现在，告诉我，你最喜欢的是哪一个人格？
EN: Instead, tell me which personality is your favorite.

CN: 嗯，那位学者24，看上去很聪明，那两撇胡子也很带感……
EN: Maybe Scholar 24? She looks very smart and has a very cute mustache...

CN: 嘁。一个只知道天天读死书的家伙。
EN: Tsk. That one only knows how to read boring books every day.

CN: 既不出门，也不锻炼，就知道想一些莫名其妙的东西。
EN: Never going out, wasting her time thinking about useless things.

CN: 最近身体发胖，睡眠变差，都是因为她！
EN: I've gained weight and my sleep has gotten worse because of her!

CN: 小丑24的笑话讲得挺好的，给我们带来了很多快乐……
EN: Maybe Clown 24? She's always telling jokes and brings joy everywhere she goes...

CN: 一个哗众取宠的烂梗大王，有什么好喜欢的？
EN: What's there to like about a crass jester desperate for even an ounce of attention?

CN: 喜欢看小丑，不如多去马戏团。照镜子也可以。
EN: If you want to see a clown that badly, go visit the circus. Or better yet, look in the mirror.

CN: 猫咪24好可爱！
EN: Cat 24 is so adorable!

CN: 咦，一个连人话都不会说的家伙，有什么好喜欢的？
EN: What's there to like about a beast that can't even speak the human language?

CN: 是因为需要宠物来填补你空洞无聊的生活吗？
EN: Are you that desperate to fill the void of your empty life that you want a glorified pet?

CN: 我知道了，你是毒舌24。
EN: It seems I'm speaking with Toxic 24.

CN: 我知道了，你一定叫做毒舌24。
EN: It seems I'm speaking with Toxic 24.

CN: 什么毒舌24！我是堂堂
EN: Toxic 24?! I'm the Dignified 24!!

CN: 最近跟詹金去街上，听到那些人吵架听多了，新生成的人格也变得这么不礼貌……
EN: Recently, I went to the slums with Jenkin. After hearing the people there trash talk so much, my newly formed personality decided to imitate their manner of speech...

CN: 请放心，守密人！我一定会尽快把这个人格教育好的！
EN: Please rest assured, Keeper! I'll make sure to teach this personality some manners!

CN: 加油……
EN: Do your best...

CN: 加油……
EN: Do your best...
